01:23:55,179 --> 01:23:56,886
I'll have a beer, please.

959
01:23:56,970 --> 01:23:58,969
- What do you want?
- A beer, please.

960
01:23:59,053 --> 01:24:01,470
You can't just waltz in here
dressed like that and ask for a beer.

961
01:24:01,553 --> 01:24:03,886
- What, is there a dress code?
- Why are you here?

962
01:24:03,970 --> 01:24:06,927
- I'm meeting someone called Natalie.
- That's me.

963
01:24:07,012 --> 01:24:09,219
Yeah. We met before, right?

964
01:24:10,595 --> 01:24:12,844
- Then why am I here?
- I don't know. Why don't you tell me.

965
01:24:12,928 --> 01:24:15,386
I don't remember. I have no
short-term memory. It's not amnesia.

966
01:24:15,471 --> 01:24:18,136
- You're the memory guy.
- How do you know about me?

967
01:24:18,970 --> 01:24:20,677
My boyfriend told me about you.

968
01:24:20,762 --> 01:24:24,677
- Yeah? Who's your boyfriend?
- Jimmy Grants. Do you know him?

969
01:24:25,845 --> 01:24:27,303
No.

970
01:24:27,387 --> 01:24:30,844
He knows you. He told me about you.

971
01:24:30,928 --> 01:24:33,011
He said you were staying at the Discount.

972
01:24:33,095 --> 01:24:36,136
In fact, a cop came by earlier,
was looking for you.

973
01:24:36,220 --> 01:24:38,386
Said he was looking for a guy
who can't remember anything...

974
01:24:38,471 --> 01:24:40,802
...wouldn't know how he got here
or what he'd done.

975
01:24:40,887 --> 01:24:43,428
Said I get a lot of guys
around here like that.

976
01:24:43,511 --> 01:24:46,969
Chronic alcoholism is one cause
of short-term memory loss.

977
01:24:49,053 --> 01:24:51,761
- Are you Teddy?
- No. My name's Leonard.

978
01:24:51,845 --> 01:24:53,969
- Did Teddy send you?
- I don't know.

979
01:24:55,553 --> 01:24:58,219
- What's happened to Jimmy?
- I don't know that either.

980
01:24:58,304 --> 01:25:00,677
- Sorry.
- You don't remember anything?

981
01:25:00,762 --> 01:25:04,094
You don't remember where you've been
or what you've just done.

982
01:25:04,179 --> 01:25:07,802
No. I can't make new memories.
Everything just fades.

983
01:25:07,887 --> 01:25:10,594
- Then why did you come here?
- I found this in my pocket.

984
01:25:13,887 --> 01:25:15,386
<i>Your pocket.</i>

985
01:25:40,012 --> 01:25:43,136
Bar bet. Care to contribute?

986
01:25:43,220 --> 01:25:45,552
- No, thanks.
- It's for a lot of money.

987
01:25:46,137 --> 01:25:49,094
Come on. Proceeds are going to charity.
Help me out.

988
01:26:01,345 --> 01:26:02,635
Thank you.

989
01:26:20,053 --> 01:26:22,136
- On the house.
- Thanks.

990
01:26:26,928 --> 01:26:29,303
It's completely fucked
because nobody believes you.

991
01:26:30,511 --> 01:26:33,761
It's amazing what a little brain damage
will do for your credibility.

992
01:26:33,845 --> 01:26:36,635
I guess it's some kind of poetic justice
for not believing Sammy.

993
01:26:36,720 --> 01:26:38,886
You know the truth
about my condition, Officer?

994
01:26:39,720 --> 01:26:41,719
You don't know anything.

995
01:26:41,803 --> 01:26:43,969
You feel angry, you don't know why.

996
01:26:44,053 --> 01:26:46,802
You feel guilty, you have no idea why.

997
01:26:47,636 --> 01:26:50,261
You could do anything and not have
the faintest idea 10 minutes later.

998
01:26:50,345 --> 01:26:52,719
Like Sammy.
What if I've done something like Sammy?

999
01:26:53,428 --> 01:26:56,677
I didn't tell you what happened
to Sammy and his wife?

1000
01:26:58,428 --> 01:27:01,594
She came to see me at my office. I thought
she was trying to catch me off guard...

1001
01:27:01,678 --> 01:27:04,594
<i>...so I didn't tell her what I really thought,
but I never said that he was faking...</i>

1002
01:27:04,678 --> 01:27:06,594
<i>...just that his condition was mental,
not physical.</i>

1003
01:27:06,678 --> 01:27:09,635
<i>I found out later that she went home
and gave Sammy his final exam.</i>

1004
01:27:11,345 --> 01:27:14,303
Sammy? It's time for my shot.

1005
01:27:30,262 --> 01:27:32,261
<i>She knew beyond a doubt that he loved her.</i>

1006
01:27:33,428 --> 01:27:35,385
<i>So she found a way to test him.</i>

1007
01:27:48,095 --> 01:27:51,677
Sammy. It's time for my shot.

1008
01:28:01,636 --> 01:28:03,677
<i>She really thought she'd call his bluff.</i>

1009
01:28:03,762 --> 01:28:05,261
There you go.

1010
01:28:05,845 --> 01:28:09,677
<i>Or she just didn't wanna live
with the things she'd put him through.</i>

1011
01:28:19,636 --> 01:28:20,635
Sammy.

1012
01:28:22,803 --> 01:28:24,927
It's time for my shot.

1013
01:28:30,386 --> 01:28:32,178
It won't hurt.

1014
01:29:16,261 --> 01:29:18,302
<i>She went into a coma and never recovered.</i>

1015
01:29:19,470 --> 01:29:22,552
<i>Sammy couldn't understand
or explain what happened.</i>

1016
01:29:24,845 --> 01:29:26,761
He's been in a home ever since.

1017
01:29:26,845 --> 01:29:29,260
<i>He doesn't even know that his wife is dead.</i>

1018
01:29:29,344 --> 01:29:32,719
I was wrong about Sammy,
and I was wrong about his wife.

1019
01:29:32,803 --> 01:29:34,719
She wasn't interested in the money.

1020
01:29:34,803 --> 01:29:36,969
She just needed to understand his problem.

1021
01:29:37,053 --> 01:29:40,469
<i>His brain didn't respond to conditioning.
But he wasn't a con man.</i>

1022
01:29:40,553 --> 01:29:43,969
<i>When she looked into his eyes,
she thought he could be the same person.</i>

1023
01:29:44,053 --> 01:29:46,427
<i>When I looked into his eyes,
I thought I saw recognition.</i>

1024
01:29:46,511 --> 01:29:48,635
Now I know. You fake it.

1025
01:29:48,720 --> 01:29:51,552
If you think you're supposed to
recognize somebody, you just pretend to.

1026
01:29:51,636 --> 01:29:54,302
<i>You bluff it to get a pat
on the head from the doctors.</i>

1027
01:29:54,928 --> 01:29:57,178
You bluff it to seem less of a freak.

1028
01:30:00,803 --> 01:30:02,510
What drug dealer?

1029
01:30:27,887 --> 01:30:31,011
- Hey, Lenny, how you doing?
- It's private back here.

1030
01:30:31,095 --> 01:30:34,094
- It's okay. We know each other. Right, kid?
- How did you know I was in here?

1031
01:30:34,178 --> 01:30:36,177
The Jag's out front.
Should have put it around back.

1032
01:30:36,261 --> 01:30:39,761
What are you still doing here, Lenny?
There's plenty of tattoo parlors up north.

1033
01:30:39,845 --> 01:30:42,343
I guess I wanted to get something down
before it slipped my mind.

1034
01:30:42,428 --> 01:30:44,886
- Give me the keys. I'll move it.
- It'll be all right for a minute.

1035
01:30:44,970 --> 01:30:46,469
Wait out there.

1036
01:30:47,303 --> 01:30:49,886
Give me a minute.
I gotta get something for you.

1037
01:30:53,636 --> 01:30:57,677
Fact six: Car license SG137IU.

1038
01:31:03,720 --> 01:31:05,969
Look. Wait a minute, will ya?

1039
01:31:09,470 --> 01:31:11,510
- We gotta get you out of here.
- Why?

1040
01:31:11,595 --> 01:31:14,886
Man. Come on, Leonard.
How many times I gotta tell you?

1041
01:31:14,970 --> 01:31:16,944
It's not safe for you
to hang around here anymore.

1042
01:31:16,945 --> 01:31:19,343
- Why not?
- Because that cop's looking for you.

1043
01:31:19,428 --> 01:31:22,011
I gotta get you a new identity,
some new clothes.

1044
01:31:22,095 --> 01:31:24,719
A different car would do for now.
So put these on.

1045
01:31:24,803 --> 01:31:26,177
What cop?

1046
01:31:27,386 --> 01:31:30,343
He's a bad cop. He's the one
that checked you into the Discount Inn.

1047
01:31:30,428 --> 01:31:32,662
He's been calling you for days,
telling you shit...

1048
01:31:32,663 --> 01:31:34,328
...slipping envelopes under your door.
Shit like that.

1049
01:31:34,344 --> 01:31:37,052
- How do you know this?
- He told me. He thinks it's funny.

1050
01:31:37,136 --> 01:31:39,135
- He's been laughing at you.
- You're full of shit.

1051
01:31:39,219 --> 01:31:42,052
I'm not. He knows you're no good
on the phone, so he's been calling you.

1052
01:31:42,136 --> 01:31:44,135
Sometimes you don't answer the phone...

1053
01:31:44,219 --> 01:31:47,011
...so he slips shit under your door to scare
you into answering the phone again...

1054
01:31:47,094 --> 01:31:49,761
...giving you a line of crap about
John G. being some local drug dealer.

1055
01:31:49,845 --> 01:31:53,093
- Jimmy Grants.
- Who's Jimmy Grants?

1056
01:31:53,178 --> 01:31:55,135
Leonard, Jimmy's the drug dealer.

1057
01:31:55,219 --> 01:31:57,510
The cop wants to know
how his operation's run.

1058
01:31:57,595 --> 01:31:59,594
He's got some score in mind.
Somehow you're involved.

1059
01:31:59,678 --> 01:32:01,343
Uh-huh. How do you know him?

1060
01:32:02,428 --> 01:32:07,135
I'm a snitch. He's a cop from out of town.
The local boys put us together.

1061
01:32:07,219 --> 01:32:09,552
If he knew I was helping you,
he'd fucking kill me.

1062
01:32:09,636 --> 01:32:13,427
So take these clothes, put them on
and get the fuck out of here.

1063
01:32:13,511 --> 01:32:16,135
Come on, Leonard. Just go.

1064
01:32:36,762 --> 01:32:38,719
You are full of shit.

1065
01:32:40,428 --> 01:32:42,594
"Come by after. Natalie."

1066
01:32:42,678 --> 01:32:44,177
"Ferdy's Bar."

1067
01:33:26,970 --> 01:33:28,302
Hey, Jimmy.

1068
01:33:31,344 --> 01:33:34,135
I'm sorry.
I thought you were somebody else.

1069
01:33:34,803 --> 01:33:36,135
Sorry.

1070
01:33:36,970 --> 01:33:38,218
That's okay.

1071
01:33:52,386 --> 01:33:55,635
So this Jimmy Grants deals drugs out of
the bar where his girlfriend works?

1072
01:33:56,470 --> 01:33:58,968
But he's not gonna bring her along.
He'll come by himself, right?

1073
01:34:00,303 --> 01:34:03,260
I always figured the drugs angle
would be the best way to get him.

1074
01:34:04,303 --> 01:34:07,469
No, Officer.
I'm as ready as I'll ever be.

1075
01:34:08,178 --> 01:34:10,719
You're in the lobby?
What do you look like?

1076
01:34:12,011 --> 01:34:13,968
I'll be right there.

1077
01:34:56,052 --> 01:34:56,968
Lenny.

1078
01:35:00,094 --> 01:35:01,302
Officer Gammell.

1079
01:35:03,845 --> 01:35:06,552
Yeah. Come on.

1080
01:35:23,052 --> 01:35:25,510
- Smile.
- Not here.

1081
01:35:26,845 --> 01:35:28,135
Over here.

1082
01:35:33,803 --> 01:35:36,802
- Is it Officer or Lieutenant Gammell?
- You know what?

1083
01:35:36,886 --> 01:35:39,093
Don't write Gammell, just Teddy.

1084
01:35:39,762 --> 01:35:41,802
- Why?
- I'm undercover.

1085
01:35:44,636 --> 01:35:47,051
This is the directions where he's going.

1086
01:35:47,136 --> 01:35:50,177
- My number's on the bottom if you need me.
- You're not coming?

1087
01:35:50,261 --> 01:35:52,177
No. It wouldn't be appropriate.

1088
01:35:56,720 --> 01:35:59,802
Nice picture. I look thin.

1089
01:36:03,511 --> 01:36:04,802
Hey, Lenny.

1090
01:36:05,470 --> 01:36:06,885
Make him beg.

1091
01:37:29,886 --> 01:37:31,135
Teddy!

1092
01:37:34,344 --> 01:37:35,843
Hey, Teddy!

1093
01:37:42,802 --> 01:37:43,968
Jimmy.

1094
01:37:45,761 --> 01:37:48,343
- What the fuck are you doing here?
- You Jimmy Grants?

1095
01:37:48,428 --> 01:37:50,427
Expecting any other Jimmys out here,
Memory Man?

1096
01:37:50,511 --> 01:37:54,760
- Do you remember me?
- Yeah, I remember you.

1097
01:37:54,844 --> 01:37:57,260
Where the fuck's Teddy?

1098
01:37:57,344 --> 01:37:58,051
Well?

1099
01:38:02,178 --> 01:38:04,968
Motherfuck... Fuckin' retard!

1100
01:38:07,094 --> 01:38:10,135
- Strip.
- You're making a big fucking mistake, pal.

1101
01:38:10,219 --> 01:38:11,510
Strip!

1102
01:38:13,595 --> 01:38:16,177
My associates are not
the kind of people you wanna piss off.

1103
01:38:16,261 --> 01:38:17,843
Don't say anything else.

1104
01:38:17,927 --> 01:38:20,343
- I knew I couldn't trust that fuck!
- Take it off.

1105
01:38:22,969 --> 01:38:24,510
Cocksucker.

1106
01:38:25,595 --> 01:38:27,385
Your pants too.

1107
01:38:28,344 --> 01:38:30,302
- Why?
- I don't wanna get blood on them.

1108
01:38:32,386 --> 01:38:34,385
Wait.
Did he tell you what I was bringing?

1109
01:38:34,470 --> 01:38:38,385
- Take your fuckin' pants off!
- I've got 200 grand stashed in the car!

1110
01:38:38,470 --> 01:38:41,177
- Just take it!
- You think you can bargain with me?

1111
01:38:41,261 --> 01:38:43,635
- Take the money and walk away!
- I don't want your fuckin' money.

1112
01:38:44,677 --> 01:38:46,135
Then what?

1113
01:38:46,677 --> 01:38:50,343
- What do you want from me?
- I want my fuckin' life back!

1114
01:40:20,844 --> 01:40:22,051
Sammy.

1115
01:40:28,844 --> 01:40:30,885
He said "Sammy".
How does he know about Sammy?

1116
01:40:30,969 --> 01:40:32,343
Oh, fuck.

1117
01:40:52,927 --> 01:40:54,926
What have I done?

1118
01:40:56,802 --> 01:40:59,510
Mister, I need help.
There's a guy in here, he's hurt bad.

1119
01:40:59,594 --> 01:41:01,843
- We gotta get him to a doctor.
- All right.

1120
01:41:03,635 --> 01:41:05,926
I don't know what happened.
I've got this memory thing.

1121
01:41:06,011 --> 01:41:08,218
- Do I know you?
- No. Don't worry. I'm a cop.

1122
01:41:09,052 --> 01:41:11,843
- Is he still breathing?
- I don't know. Maybe.

1123
01:41:11,927 --> 01:41:14,469
What the hell were you guys
doing down here?

1124
01:41:16,011 --> 01:41:18,093
I don't remember.
I have this condition.

1125
01:41:18,178 --> 01:41:20,885
I hope it's not as serious as his,
'cause this guy's dead.

1126
01:41:20,969 --> 01:41:23,509
Ow! Lenny! That shit kills!

1127
01:41:23,594 --> 01:41:27,135
So you remember me now, huh?
You are a fuckin' cop.

1128
01:41:27,219 --> 01:41:30,051
Yeah. And I'm the guy
that helped you find him.

1129
01:41:30,136 --> 01:41:32,010
Get up. Get up.

1130
01:41:32,094 --> 01:41:34,135
Lenny, you got the wrong idea.

1131
01:41:36,844 --> 01:41:38,885
Who is that? He knew me.

1132
01:41:38,969 --> 01:41:41,593
Of course he did. He raped your wife.
He fucked up your brain.

1133
01:41:41,677 --> 01:41:43,718
Bullshit. He's not the guy.

1134
01:41:43,802 --> 01:41:48,135
His name is James F. Grants.
John G. Check your tattoos.

1135
01:41:48,219 --> 01:41:50,634
- What was he bringing the 200 grand for?
- What?

1136
01:41:52,219 --> 01:41:55,010
- What was it for?
- A load of amphetamines I told him I had.

1137
01:41:55,094 --> 01:41:58,551
- Is this a drug deal?
- No. Yeah, that and your thing.

1138
01:41:58,635 --> 01:42:02,260
Look, Leonard, Jimmy's your guy. I just
figured we'd make a few dollars on the side.

1139
01:42:02,344 --> 01:42:05,968
- How did he know me?
- The Discount Inn. He dealt out of there.

1140
01:42:06,052 --> 01:42:09,343
The guy at the front desk let him know
if anybody came snooping around.

1141
01:42:09,428 --> 01:42:11,968
He called Jimmy the minute he saw you
taking a picture of the dump.

1142
01:42:12,052 --> 01:42:14,427
- You're fucking using me.
- No! You get half!

1143
01:42:14,510 --> 01:42:17,135
He knew about Sammy!
Why would I tell him about fuckin' Sammy?

1144
01:42:17,219 --> 01:42:20,593
You tell everybody about Sammy,
everybody who'll listen.

1145
01:42:20,677 --> 01:42:22,801
"Remember Sammy Jankis?"
"Remember Sammy Jankis?"

1146
01:42:22,886 --> 01:42:25,801
Great story.
Gets better every time you tell it.

1147
01:42:26,761 --> 01:42:28,676
So you lie to yourself to be happy.

1148
01:42:28,761 --> 01:42:30,801
There's nothing wrong with that.
We all do it.

1149
01:42:30,886 --> 01:42:34,010
Who cares if there's a few little details
you'd rather not remember?

1150
01:42:36,469 --> 01:42:38,801
- What the fuck are you talking about?
- I don't know.

1151
01:42:39,594 --> 01:42:41,509
Your wife surviving the assault.

1152
01:42:42,303 --> 01:42:44,218
Her not believing your condition.

1153
01:42:44,303 --> 01:42:48,468
The torment and pain and anguish
tearing her up inside.

1154
01:42:49,052 --> 01:42:50,343
The insulin.

1155
01:42:51,635 --> 01:42:54,343
That's Sammy, not me.
I told you about Sammy.

1156
01:42:54,427 --> 01:42:57,426
Yeah, right.
Like you tell yourself over and over again.

1157
01:42:57,510 --> 01:42:59,509
Conditioning yourself to remember.

1158
01:42:59,594 --> 01:43:02,177
- Learning through repetition.
- Sammy let his wife kill herself.

1159
01:43:02,261 --> 01:43:07,302
- Sammy ended up in an institution.
- Sammy was a con man, a faker.

1160
01:43:07,386 --> 01:43:09,551
I never said that Sammy was faking.

1161
01:43:10,136 --> 01:43:12,593
You exposed him for what he was... a fraud.

1162
01:43:12,677 --> 01:43:14,634
But I was wrong.
That's the whole point.

1163
01:43:16,303 --> 01:43:19,051
- See, Sammy's wife came to me.
- Sammy didn't have a wife.

1164
01:43:21,802 --> 01:43:24,135
<i>It was your wife who had diabetes.</i>

1165
01:43:30,510 --> 01:43:31,509
Ouch.

1166
01:43:34,136 --> 01:43:35,801
My wife wasn't diabetic.

1167
01:43:36,802 --> 01:43:38,218
You sure?

1168
01:43:43,011 --> 01:43:46,135
- Ouch. Cut it out.
- She wasn't diabetic.

1169
01:43:47,136 --> 01:43:50,926
You think I don't know my own wife?
What the fuck is wrong with you?

1170
01:43:51,011 --> 01:43:54,426
I guess I can only make you remember
the things you wanna be true.

1171
01:43:54,510 --> 01:43:56,885
- Like old Jimmy down there.
- He's not the right guy.

1172
01:43:56,969 --> 01:43:59,135
He was to you.

1173
01:43:59,219 --> 01:44:02,634
Come on. You got your revenge.
Enjoy it while you still remember.

1174
01:44:02,719 --> 01:44:05,218
What difference does it make
whether he was your guy or not?

1175
01:44:05,303 --> 01:44:07,926
- It makes all the difference.
- Why? You're never gonna know.

1176
01:44:08,011 --> 01:44:09,302
- Yes, I will.
- No, you won't.

1177
01:44:09,385 --> 01:44:10,843
I will. Somehow I'll know.

1178
01:44:10,927 --> 01:44:11,744
You won't remember!

1179
01:44:11,745 --> 01:44:13,342
When it's done, I will know.
It'll be different.

1180
01:44:13,427 --> 01:44:17,342
I thought so too.
In fact, I was sure of it, but you didn't!

1181
01:44:20,136 --> 01:44:23,384
That's right. The real John G.

1182
01:44:23,469 --> 01:44:27,051
I helped you find him over a year ago.
He's already dead.

1183
01:44:27,136 --> 01:44:30,010
- Don't lie to me anymore.
- Look, Lenny.

1184
01:44:30,635 --> 01:44:33,509
I was the cop assigned to your wife's case.
I believed you.

1185
01:44:33,594 --> 01:44:36,135
I thought you deserved a chance for revenge.

1186
01:44:36,219 --> 01:44:39,509
I'm the one that helped you find the
other guy in your bathroom that night...

1187
01:44:39,594 --> 01:44:41,926
...the guy that cracked your skull
and fucked your wife.

1188
01:44:42,011 --> 01:44:44,468
We found him. You killed him.

1189
01:44:46,136 --> 01:44:51,468
But you didn't remember.
So I helped you start looking again...

1190
01:44:51,552 --> 01:44:53,801
...looking for the guy
you already killed.

1191
01:44:54,343 --> 01:44:56,093
Yeah? So who was he?

1192
01:44:56,178 --> 01:44:58,551
Just some guy.
Does it even matter who?

1193
01:44:59,302 --> 01:45:03,177
No reason, Lenny. No conspiracy.
Just bad fucking luck.

1194
01:45:04,385 --> 01:45:08,135
Couple of junkies too strung out
to realize your wife didn't live alone.

1195
01:45:09,302 --> 01:45:13,093
But when you killed him,
I was so convinced that you'd remember.

1196
01:45:13,677 --> 01:45:15,634
But it didn't stick.

1197
01:45:15,719 --> 01:45:18,468
Like nothing ever sticks.
Like this won't stick.

1198
01:45:23,136 --> 01:45:27,760
I took that picture...
just when you did it.

1199
01:45:29,761 --> 01:45:31,676
Look how happy you are.

1200
01:45:33,011 --> 01:45:34,760
I wanted to see that face again.

1201
01:45:34,844 --> 01:45:37,634
- Gee, thanks.
- Fuck you.

1202
01:45:37,719 --> 01:45:41,468
I gave you a reason to live,
and you were more than happy to help.

1203
01:45:41,552 --> 01:45:45,718
You don't want the truth.
You make up your own truth.

1204
01:45:45,802 --> 01:45:47,760
Like your police file.

1205
01:45:48,594 --> 01:45:51,593
It was complete when I gave it to you.
Who took out the 12 pages?

1206
01:45:51,677 --> 01:45:54,218
- You, probably.
- No, it wasn't me. See, it was you.

1207
01:45:54,302 --> 01:45:58,010
- Why would I do that?
- To create a puzzle you could never solve.

1208
01:45:58,094 --> 01:46:00,010
You know how many towns?

1209
01:46:00,094 --> 01:46:02,259
How many John G.'s or James G.'s?

1210
01:46:02,343 --> 01:46:04,384
Shit, Lenny. I'm a fucking John G.

1211
01:46:04,469 --> 01:46:07,718
- Your name is Teddy.
- My mother calls me Teddy.

1212
01:46:07,802 --> 01:46:10,676
My name's John Edward Gammell.

1213
01:46:10,761 --> 01:46:11,801
Cheer up.

1214
01:46:11,886 --> 01:46:14,634
There's plenty of John G.'s for us to find.

1215
01:46:18,011 --> 01:46:20,426
All you do is moan.

1216
01:46:20,510 --> 01:46:22,843
I'm the one that has to live
with what you've done.

1217
01:46:22,927 --> 01:46:24,634
I'm the one that put it all together.

1218
01:46:24,719 --> 01:46:29,384
You wander around, you're playing detective.
You're living a dream, kid.

1219
01:46:29,469 --> 01:46:33,551
A dead wife to pine for.
A sense of purpose to your life.

1220
01:46:33,635 --> 01:46:36,968
A romantic quest that you wouldn't end
even if I wasn't in the picture.

1221
01:46:38,260 --> 01:46:41,426
- I should kill you.
- Quit it. Lenny, come on.

1222
01:46:41,510 --> 01:46:44,509
You're not a killer.
That's why you're so good at it.

1223
01:46:48,052 --> 01:46:50,801
What are you doing?
You know what time it is?

1224
01:46:50,886 --> 01:46:52,968
It's beer o'clock. I'm buying.

1225
01:46:54,969 --> 01:46:56,093
Fuck.

1226
01:47:06,177 --> 01:47:07,301
I'm not a killer.

1227
01:47:08,594 --> 01:47:11,135
I'm just someone who wanted
to make things right.

1228
01:47:17,177 --> 01:47:19,551
Can I just let myself forget
what you've told me?

1229
01:47:36,761 --> 01:47:40,134
Can I just let myself forget
what you made me do?

1230
01:47:54,385 --> 01:47:56,134
You think I just want
another puzzle to solve?

1231
01:47:56,969 --> 01:47:59,134
Another John G. to look for?

1232
01:48:00,343 --> 01:48:02,217
You're a John G.

1233
01:48:03,927 --> 01:48:06,010
So you can be my John G.

1234
01:48:14,469 --> 01:48:16,593
Do I lie to myself to be happy?

1235
01:48:17,886 --> 01:48:19,634
In your case, Teddy...

1236
01:48:20,761 --> 01:48:22,676
...yes, I will.

1237
01:48:35,802 --> 01:48:37,885
Hey, that's not your car!

1238
01:48:37,969 --> 01:48:40,551
- It is now.
- Jesus Christ, you can't take it!

1239
01:48:40,635 --> 01:48:43,551
- Why not?
- Because the guy you just killed owns it!

1240
01:48:43,635 --> 01:48:45,342
Somebody'll recognize it!

1241
01:48:46,802 --> 01:48:49,885
I think I'd rather be mistaken
for a dead guy than a killer.

1242
01:48:50,844 --> 01:48:53,342
I might hang on to this for a while.

1243
01:48:54,177 --> 01:48:55,468
Lenny.

1244
01:48:57,510 --> 01:49:00,010
Will you help me find the keys?

1245
01:49:00,093 --> 01:49:01,843
Help me find my keys.

1246
01:49:24,093 --> 01:49:27,384
I have to believe in a world
outside my own mind.

1247
01:49:27,469 --> 01:49:29,634
I have to believe that
my actions still have meaning...

1248
01:49:29,719 --> 01:49:31,676
...even if I can't remember them.

1249
01:49:33,844 --> 01:49:36,509
I have to believe
that when my eyes are closed...

1250
01:49:36,594 --> 01:49:38,676
...the world's still here.

1251
01:49:39,886 --> 01:49:42,301
Do I believe the world's still here?

1252
01:49:45,218 --> 01:49:46,801
Is it still out there?

1253
01:49:50,635 --> 01:49:51,634
Yeah.

1254
01:49:54,010 --> 01:49:56,801
We all need mirrors
to remind ourselves who we are.

1255
01:49:59,135 --> 01:50:00,843
I'm no different.

1256
01:50:14,135 --> 01:50:15,925
Now, where was I?

